        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 7:27PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 727 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of East Glacier Park Village, or 44 miles southwest of
Cut Bank, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Browning, East Glacier Park Village, South Browning, East Glacier
Park, North Browning, and Starr School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
